# Prettier is deliberately scoped to CSS (see .prettierrc + the `format:css` script).
#
# The TS/TSX surface is NOT uniformly Prettier-formatted and must not be swept in:
# the grouped UI-kit bundles (ui.tsx, cards.tsx, sections-home.tsx) are hand-kept in
# a compact style with long single-line JSX, while lt.ts/en.ts ARE conformant at the
# default printWidth 80. One `prettier --write .` would rewrite both groups and bury
# any real change in an unreviewable diff.
#
# Listed by extension rather than `*` + negations: gitignore semantics cannot
# re-include a path whose parent directory is excluded, so the `*` / `!*.css` form
# silently ignores everything (it did — it made `--check` pass on zero files).
#
# If the repo ever adopts repo-wide formatting, do it as its own commit and update
# this file. Do not let it ride along with a feature change.
*.ts
*.tsx
*.js
*.jsx
*.mjs
